{"title_page": "TMI News", "text_new": "{{short description|South Korean news show}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name       = TMI News\n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| native_name     = \n| genre           = {{ubl|[[Variety show]]|News Show}}\n| creator         = \n| director        = \n| starring        = {{ubl|[[Jun Hyun-moo]]|[[Jang Do-yeon]]|}}\n| country         = South Korea\n| language        = Korean\n| num_seasons     = 1\n| num_episodes    = 36 (as of April 8, 2020)\n| list_episodes   = \n| producer        = \n| location        = South Korea\n| cinematography  = \n| editor          = \n| camera          = \n| runtime         = 60 minutes\n| company         = \n| distributor     = \n| network         = [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]\n| picture_format  = \n| audio_format    = \n| first_aired     = {{start date|2019|4|25}}\n| last_aired      = present\n| website         = https://www.genie.co.kr/genietv/broadcastDetail/568\n}}\n\n'''''TMI News''''' ({{Korean|TMI \ub274\uc2a4}}) is a [[South Korea]]n news [[variety show]] that airs on [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]] every Thursday at 20:00 ([[Korean Standard Time|KST]]) starting from April 25, 2019 until May 30, 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uc804\ud604\ubb34X\ubc15\uc900\ud615X\uc724\ubcf4\ubbf8X\ub518\ub518, \uc5e0\ub137 \u2018TMI NEWS\u2019 MC \ubc1c\ud0c1 [\uacf5\uc2dd]|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=469&aid=0000381340|accessdate=April 17, 2019|work=Hankook Ilbo|date=April 24, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nThe show went on a hiatus without notice, but it returned on July 31, 2019 and currently airs on every Wednesday at 20:00 ([[Korean Standard Time|KST]]).<ref name=tmi2>{{cite news|title=\u2018TMI NEWS\u2019 \uc544\uc774\ub3cc \ucc28\ud2b8\uc1fc\ub85c \uc0c8\ub2e8\uc7a5, \uc804\ud604\ubb34X\uc7a5\ub3c4\uc5f0 MC \ud638\ud761(\uacf5\uc2dd)|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=609&aid=0000140787|accessdate=July 17, 2019|work=Newsen|date=July 17, 2019|language=ko}}</ref> The show had a hiatus after the episode on November 27, 2019, and returned again starting January 15, 2020.\n\n== Program ==\nThe show is the first ever global [[K-pop]] idols' news & talk show. The \"TMI\" in the show's name stands for '''T'''hursday '''M'''net '''I'''dol. The show is currently retrieving any possible TMI (Too Much Information) information from the public about the idol groups or their individual members through their online form, and the information that will be used for the show is \"news reported\" on the show.<ref>{{cite web|title=Introduction to TMI News|url=http://tv.mnet.com/program/2129/menu/360}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Online form to submit information for TMI News|url=https://form.office.naver.com/form/responseView.cmd?formkey=ZWE2MWYwMTktNzY1My00YmNlLTk0N2MtNmIxZmEwZjg3ZmEz}}</ref>\n\nFrom episode 7, the show was revamped into a chart show.<ref name=tmi2/>\n\n== Cast ==\n===Current===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! Name\n! Role & Character\n! Episode\n! Ref.\n|-\n| [[Jun Hyun-moo]]\n| Main Anchor\n| 1 - present\n| <ref name=tmicast>{{cite web|title=Cast of TMI News|url=http://tv.mnet.com/program/2129/menu/368}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Jang Do-yeon]]\n| Main Anchor\n| 7 - present\n| \n|-\n|}\n\n===Former===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! Name\n! Role & Character\n! Episode\n! Ref.\n|-\n| [[Joon Park|Park Joon-hyung]] ([[g.o.d]])\n| Reporter; idol's \"Archaeopteryx\" and a reporter who has a \"my way\" feel\n| 1 - 6\n| rowspan=\"4\" | <ref name=tmicast/>\n|-\n| [[DinDin]]\n| Reporter; with his Too Much Super Insider ability, he guides to rise himself from a low tide\n| 2 - 6\n|-\n| [[Yoon Bo-mi]] ([[Apink]])\n| Reporter; checking facts with her current occupation of being an idol\n| 1 - 6\n|-\n| Soobin ([[Cosmic Girls]])\n| TMI Weather Caster; TMI News' multi-player, Human Peach Caster\n| 1 - 24\n|-\n|}\n\n==Episodes==\n===2019===\n{{hidden begin\n|title = List of episodes (episode 1\u201324)\n|titlestyle = backgroun